examples: New towns were constructed to accommodate overspill from established cities.

verbs.description: overspill (third-person singular simple present overspills, present participle overspilling, simple past and past participle overspilled or overspilt)

entries.meaning: To spill over, to overflow, to spill out of.
examples: Further, Coventry's prosperity and rapid growth was threatening that it as well as Birmingham would require to overspill its boundaries.
